A happy destiny is God's best gift to man3 but even as Chance crusheth the good if she come with a load of woe, so she maketh the wicked eminent if she win her way. Honour hath various shapes, and myriad are the kinds of human prowess3 yet one outstandeth all, and it is his whom a just mind guides in what lieth to his hand. The deep misery of battle is no place for the voice of the lyre and the clear-ringing dance, nor hath the clash of bronze with bronze to do with merrymaking; rather in every act of man is the right time the best, and God too prospereth him that doeth a thing well.
